        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31371",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "According to documentation $context is part of Zend_Form and not of Zend_Validate.\n\nZend_Validate does for now not support $context as this feature does not match to all validators.\nThis Zend_Form feature is not part of the interface of Zend_Validate. Maybe in future but not for now.\n\n@Matthew:\nDo you want to change documentation to reflect this like in the other issue ?\nOtherwise I would propose to close this issue as there is already a feature request.\n\nMy opinion is that context should not be added to Zend_Validate's interface. It would not match for most of the available validators. What should a \"Int\" or \"Date\" validator do with $context ?\nAlso some validators already provide a second argument which is used differently than context. They would all have to be rewritten. This could also apply to user-land validators.\n\nAccording to Zend_Form validation and context I was said that I have to add a new form-validator which would then also support context additionally to form element validation. But this would be one or more specialized form validators for form elements and not all other standard validators.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-27T00:50:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-27T00:50:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31375",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If $context is added as an *optional* argument, it does not break the interface, and this is in fact how we document using the $context variable within the Zend_Form documentation. Simply modify your code slightly:\n\n{code}\nclass MyValidator extends Zend_Validate_Abstract\n{\n    public function isValid($value, $context = null)\n    {\n        if (null === $context) {\n            \/\/ optionally, you can make it required via logical conditions...\n            throw new Exception('This validator requires a context array');\n        }\n        \/\/ ...\n    }\n}\n{code}\n\nThere is no need for additional validator interfaces or abstract classes with this strategy.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-27T05:35:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-27T05:35:30.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
